# Cloudflare Pages redirects file.
# Format: <source>  <destination>  [<status>]
#   - Status defaults to 301 (permanent) if omitted.
#   - Lines starting with `#` are comments.
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
#
# Future categories (add entries below as the site grows):
#   1. Legacy URLs            — redirect old paths kept for inbound link equity
#   2. Language fallbacks     — `/<lang>/missing-page` → `/missing-page`
#   3. Marketing aliases      — short campaign URLs → canonical product pages
#   4. Trailing-slash cleanup — handled by `trailingSlash: 'never'` in
#                                astro.config.ts; only override here for exceptions
#
# Keep redirect chains to a maximum of one hop for SEO. Always 301
# (permanent) for legacy URLs; 302 (temporary) only for short-lived
# campaigns.
